comments.message:
nit, extra parens.  Same thing on the second statement.

Can we break this up a little so the logic is more clear?

if (threshIface.second){
   if (!thresIface.second->initialize(true)){
       std::cerr << "Error initializing threshold interface \n";
   }
}

> In the above if condition, I have checked the threshold level and direction for each sensor in findOrder() function. This function will verify whether the level is present in the thresProp array. If the level is not present, it will continue and read next threshold. So the range check will be verified in that function.


I don't see any code that compares thresholdInterfaces.size() against any index, which is what's being asked here.  Even if there was in a different scope, that's non obvious that this code can't seg fault, and we should duplicate the range check here as well.

All I'm asking is for

size_t index = static_cast<size_t>(threshold.level);
if (index >= thresholdInterfaces.size()){
   std::cout << "Got bad level";
   return;
}


PS, also, this should be cast to size_t, not int.

The below line is also present in Thresholds.cpp file in 2 places, therefore, I have used function to make it common and returned interfaces directly from that function.

        std::shared_ptr<sdbusplus::asio::dbus_interface>& interface =
            sensor->thresholdInterfaces[static_cast<size_t>(threshold.level)];
